Hey, I'm a videographer and I'm looking to begin plans for a creative project inspired by the new release of Wuthering Heights which would be filmed in Dartmoor 

Looking for a male and female model, a stylist and open to anyone who'd like to contribute to the project

It will be a creative, collaborative project, so being transparent that there will be no payments involved.

So far this is a concept, awaiting approval from Dartmoor National Park, but if anyone is looking to get into acting / modelling or any role within the filmmaking industry this could be a great opportunity to be part of a breathtaking project

Whether you‚Äôre already planning your sweepstakes or you might tolerate the odd match, we‚Äôd love to hear from you. We want to capture the general public from all walks of life and approaches to football.

Talent must be comfortable on set as well as self-shooting.

items.text:
Hello! I am looking for actors to audition for my University of Colorado Colorado Springs (UCCS) Capstone Student Short Film. I am a senior Digital Filmmaking major.

**Production Title:**‚Äã Beyond the Door
**Genre: **Comedy, drama, teen/young adult
**Log Line/Short Film Synopsis:‚Äã**

An adventurous college student‚Äôs fixation on opening a mysterious door becomes a comedic test of friendship, nostalgia, and fear of growing up.

**Character Breakdowns -**

**Conner (18-25 years old) - Male, any ethnicity**
An adventurous and goofy spirit who wants more than anything to escape the fears of growing up by opening a mystical door. Conner later realizes his friends provide the support and connection he needs to face growing up.

**Mike (20-26 years old) - Male, any ethnicity**
A weeb and gamer at heart (who would rather be at home), Mike thinks Conner‚Äôs pursuits are stupid and childish, although he is somewhat jealous of his happiness. After insulting Conner and pushing him to his limits by breaking his map he learns he really has been an absolute jerk.

**Henry (20-26 years old) - Male, any ethnicity**

The more supportive friend of Conner‚Äôs who helps mediate between him and Mike. He is the supreme nerd with black glasses who owns all the hot new latest Shroom Kart and Party games. Henry is the one who forced Mike to come on this adventure in the first place to lift Conner‚Äôs spirit.

**Director:‚Äã** Harrison Mallane
**Production Type:** Student Short Film
**Contact Information:** [BeyondTheDoorProductions@gmail.com
](mailto:BeyondTheDoorProductions@gmail.com)**Run Time:** Short Film
**Compensation:** Non-paid, Meals, Film Credit, Copy of Film, Copy of Footage
**Pay & Union:** Non-Paid, Non-Union
**Audition Date**: Sun. Feb 22, 2026, 11am - 7pm Audition
**Audition Location:** UCCS Campus - El Pomar Center 103 (directions will be sent by email)
**Auditions are by appointment only**. You can sign up for an audition time here:
[https://calendly.com/jayhubert/2026-uccscapstone-auditions-february-22
](https://calendly.com/jayhubert/2026-uccscapstone-auditions-february-22)**Shooting Schedule/Production Date:** April 5th (Easter Sunday) Please be available for the entire day. Rehearsal dates and times will be decided with the film crew after actors are selected.
**Filming Location:** In the near Colorado Springs area will be in a park or wooded area.
**Project Description:** UCCS Capstone Student Short Film

If you have any questions, please email Harry and Aiden at [BeyondTheDoorProductions@gmail.com](mailto:BeyondTheDoorProductions@gmail.com) If you have a headshot and acting resume, please feel free to attach them to your email, though they are not required.

Please see the poster attached below and Jay‚Äôs post for additional information and clarity.

UCCS Digital Filmmaking Capstone Film Casting Call

Hello! I am looking for actors to audition for my UCCS Capstone Student Short Film. Details below:

Title: Unforced Errors

Genre: Drama

Logline: Matt is convinced his recently deceased father loved his brother more than him, but his brother Josh unknowingly feels the same way. As Matt searches for his dad‚Äôs old baseball card collection, the brothers soon discover that their father‚Äôs love was unconditional.

Roles: 

**Matt (20 ‚Äì 26 years old) - Male, Any Ethnicity:**

Matt is a true younger brother. He is always trying his best to impress everyone around him and make himself noticed, but he never feels like he is good enough. He loves his brother Josh, but he has always been jealous of his relationship with their father.

 

**Josh (22 ‚Äì 28 years old) - Male, Any Ethnicity:**

Josh was a high school baseball athlete, but not the jock/bully type. He has a strong exterior demeanor that hides how he truly feels: like he was never good enough for his professional baseball-playing father. While he would never want to admit it, he is jealous of his younger brother Matt and the relationship he had with their father.

Director: Zion Wilson

Producer: Onyx Riccelli

Production Type: Student Film

Contact Information: unforcederrorsfilm@gmail.com

Run Time: Short

Compensation: Non-Paid

Union Status: Non-Union

Audition Date: Saturday, February 14th, 11am-7pm. 

Audition Location:** **UCCS Campus: El Pomar Center 103 (directions are included in the appointment confirmation).

Auditions are by appointment only. Please use the link included in the attached casting call to sign up for a time slot.

Shooting Schedule: Saturday, March 7th. Please be available for the entire day.

Project Description: UCCS Capstone Student Short Film

Please email us at unforcederrorsfilm@gmail.com if you have any questions. Thank you!

Please consider helping in anyway you can.

**SHORT FILM CASTING CALL - ‚ÄúTAKEAWAYS‚Äù**

**OPEN TO UNION & NON-UNION - VOLUNTEER/UNPAID**

**DIRECTOR:** Jamie Lam

**CATEGORY:** Independent Short Film - UBCP ULB

**CASTING DIRECTOR:** Cathy Huynh

**COMPENSATION:** Volunteer/Unpaid. Food provided on set. Copy of film. IMDB credit.

**FILMING DATES/LOCATION:** March 21-22, 2026 (TBC) / Vancouver, BC

**SUBMISSION INSTRUCTIONS:** Please email **takeawaysfilm@gmail.com** with the subject heading

**[Your Name - Role Name]** and include your headshot/photo, resume and demo reel (if applicable)

**LOGLINE:** A reluctant young boy working at his family‚Äôs restaurant learns to step up as his father quietly falls apart after his loss.

**ANDY ‚Äî Male, 10-15, Chinese or East Asian-identifying.** Smart but apathetic, Andy is tired of helping out at the family restaurant, much rather preferring to play PC games at home. Even so, he takes after his dad Sam, embodying kindness and warmth when times get tough - LEAD. CANTONESE PROFICIENCY IS A PLUS.

**SAM ‚Äî Male, 40-50, Chinese or East Asian-identifying.** A caring and kind father, Sam owns and operates the family restaurant. His wife left him a year ago, leaving him to take care of Andy and the restaurant by himself. He grapples with being a good father while trying to manage his own grief - LEAD. MUST SPEAK FLUENT CANTONESE.

**FEMALE CUSTOMER ‚Äî Female, 35-45, Chinese or East Asian-identifying.** This female customers a regular at Sam‚Äôs restaurant. While paying for her food, she praises Andy for being such a well-brought up kid. 2 lines, 1 scene.

**FEMALE CUSTOMER‚ÄôS DAUGHTER ‚Äî Female, 5-10, Chinese or East Asian-identifying.** This young girl accompanies her mother to the restaurant. No lines, 1 scene.

**LINDA ‚Äî Female, 40-50, Chinese or East Asian-identifying.** Linda is Sam‚Äôs ex-wife. She is seen happily walking with another man, as Sam watches from his restaurant‚Äôs window. No lines, 1 scene.

**YOUNG BOYS ‚Äî Male, 10-15, Open ethnicity.** These young boys wave at Andy while he works at the restaurant. No lines, 1 scene.

items.text:
Auditions
Waiting for the Parade
by John Murrell
Don't miss your chance to audition for Pivot Theatre's upcoming production of this Canadian classic!
The word 
Director:Kayt Roth
Producer:The Pivot Theatre Team
Audition Dates:
February 22, 2026 at 12:00 pm
February 23, 2026 at 7:00 pm
Audition Venue: 
Progress Lab 1422 (1422 William Street, Vancouver)
Audition Requirements: 
Auditions will be cold reads from the script
Production Dates: 
April 11 and 12, 2026

Show Venue: 
Progress Lab 1422 (1422 William Street, Vancouver)
Rehearsals:
First rehearsal Wednesday, February 25, 2026, then Tuesday and Thursday evenings and all day Saturdays beginning March 3, 2026.
Synopsis:          
On the home front in Calgary during World War II, five women deal with loneliness, infidelity, heartbreak, and friendship as they support the troops, the Red Cross, and each other. This play showcases the women who stayed behind, and focuses on the effect that the war has on them, their relationships, and their families.
Characters Required:
CATHERINE (F, late 20s to early 30s): Her husband is off fighting in Europe. Practical and easygoing, works against his wishes to make ends meet. Singing ability an asset.
JANET (F, mid to late 30s): Uptight. Thinks she‚Äôs in charge. Her husband was excluded from active duty, so she tries twice as hard to make up for it by managing every aspect of local war effort programs. Piano playing and singing ability an asset.
MARGARET (F, mid-40s to 50s): A widow. Religious. Exhausted, with no use for Janet. Worries constantly about dying running in her family, and about her two adult sons, a sailor and a Communist. Singing ability an asset.
EVE (F, 20s): A teacher. In love with screen star Leslie Howard, and unhappy with her much older husband. A na√Øve optimist who is stuck between a war that might last years and a husband eager to, but unable to fight. Throws herself into her work supporting the troops. Singing ability an asset.
MARTA (F, late 20s-early 30s): German-Canadian seamstress. Dealing with her father‚Äôs arrest as a Nazi sympathizer and being ostracized by the community. Singing ability an asset. German accent a must.
 
Notes:  
Auditions are on a first come, first served basis. Actors will be seen in the order they arrive.
Roles are open to everyone regardless of background, race, gender, orientation, or ability. We encourage everyone to audition as we will be casting whoever is best for the role.
Auditions will be cold readings from the script. Actors are encouraged to read the script on their own prior to auditioning. (Note: director will not provide copies of the script.)
Please bring a r√©sum√© and headshot to auditions
This is a NON-EQUITY, volunteer production
Please forward questions to hq@pivottheatre.ca.
 
See you there!
Your Pivot Theatre Team
Pivot Theatre
1422 William Street, Vancouver, BC
 facebook  instagram
To unsubscribe from these emails, please click here.
Unsubscribe
 Sent by MailerLite

Currently casting for online content GAME SHOW. (PAID)

I am looking for the following

SECRET INVESTORS
* Do you have an ISA that is worth a substantial amount? (¬£500k+) 
* Have you always secretly invested? 
* Have you been successful in stocks and shares?

We are looking for REAL PEOPLE who want to compete in a social experiment disguised as a game show. Five real people stand in a line, and a host and guest have to rank them based on who they think has the most wealth. And the twist is ‚Äî one of the five is secretly sitting on serious savings built through investing over time.

It‚Äôs designed to challenge stereotypes around money in Britain ‚Äî the idea that wealth isn‚Äôt always flashy.

It would film in a studio near London / Elstree, and the fee is ¬£250 plus ¬£50 travel.

A key part of the format is open conversations about money ‚Äî salary ranges, spending, savings, investing, and where relevant debt. Nothing exploitative, but honest.

Message me for more details

Casting : "Maybe its love, maybe not"

I am Thomas Goersch from Stuttgart Germany. 
Actor and Filmdirector. 
I am making Independent Movies.
I present my movies on International Film festivals and was lucky to receive some awards. 
But the work is not about awards and money, its about making movies for the people to think about.
My next movie is a modern love story:
An elderly man is meeting another younger, very attractive man in the Internet.  But they are from different Continents. They start a long distance relastionship ship. which is full of passion and desire. 
One day the younger man starts to ask for money, cause he is a Student and no more able to pay his bills. 
The older man is full of distrust.
Is he only there  to pay his lovers bills or is there love between them ?
A story with two endings.
One with true love and one with only cheating. Based on a real story.
I am looking for the young attraktive Lover.
Men  25 to 42 years old,  good looking  who is able to film his parts on his own by smartshone
I am always open and honest. You can earn no money on this. but maybe there is a good film in the end promoting for you.
I guess its not necessary that an educated actor is playing this part. so feel free to get in touch
Thats me 
www.imdb.com/name/nm1591928
Get in touch under Thomas.Goersch@vodafonemail.de 
please ask for details.

items.text:
Looking to cast a lead role in our student film
please email r.khosssa-kulair23@lipa.ac.uk or DM betterman.lipa on instagram for more information ! 

HARRISON ‚Äî Supporting Lead (Male)

Playing Age: 22‚Äì30ÔøΩAccent: Neutral British (flexible)ÔøΩRole Type: Charismatic / Psychological / Romantic-ThrillerÔøΩScreen Time: High Supporting (appears throughout film)

Character Summary:ÔøΩHarrison is magnetic, calm and intensely perceptive ‚Äî the kind of person who seems to understand you before you speak. He appears in Emma‚Äôs life at her lowest moment and becomes her emotional anchor‚Ä¶ or possibly something far more dangerous. His kindness feels genuine, but always carries an unsettling edge. The audience should never be entirely sure whether he is protector, manipulator, or both.

He rarely raises his voice. Instead, his power comes from stillness, eye contact and emotional precision. His presence shifts a room ‚Äî comforting one moment, quietly threatening the next.

Performance Style:ÔøΩNaturalistic and restrained. The actor must communicate subtext and tension through micro-expressions, pauses and controlled body language rather than overt emotion.

Key Traits:

* Quiet confidence

* Observant and emotionally intelligent

* Gentle but subtly possessive

* Romantic with unsettling undertones

* Ambiguous morality

Character Arc:ÔøΩBegins as a mysterious stranger offering comfort, gradually embedding himself into Emma‚Äôs life. As events escalate, his protectiveness becomes increasingly intense, blurring the line between care and control. 

Script Better Man

Actor Notes:ÔøΩLooking for an actor comfortable playing duality ‚Äî warm and safe on the surface, but capable of conveying underlying danger without melodrama. Think: intimate psychological tension rather than overt villainy.

Comparable Tone (not impersonation):ÔøΩJoe Goldberg (You), Tom Ripley, early Patrick Bateman charm without the camp

items.text:
Hey folks, so here‚Äôs my little pitch, I suppose! I‚Äôd introduce myself, but the profile is right there;

Actually, scratch that, it feels weird starting without at least my first name. I‚Äôm Will! I‚Äôve been a lifelong creative, attending several drama schools in my twenties and continuously writing scripts that I‚Äôve often abandoned halfway through.

However, no longer! I set myself a goal this year of writing 6 short films, each with a different theme and genre, in an anthology style akin to Inside No. 9 or Black Mirror.

As a result, I‚Äôm very pleased to showcase the first finished screenplay with a short synopsis here and potentially cast the project as follows;

DISCLAIMER:

**THIS PROJECT CONTAINS VERY STRONG & MATURE THEMES NOT LIMITED TO BUT INCLUDING SEXUAL REFERENCES, PROFANITY & SELF-HARM. PLEASE ONLY APPLY IF YOU ARE 18+ AND ARE NOT SENSITIVE TO THIS MATERIAL. **
**(UNPAID OPPORTUNITY)**

**LOCATIONS: NORTH LIVERPOOL AREA.**

Synopsis:

A lonely thirty-something following a bad breakup stumbles across a group of paranormal investigators who have a very different take on what life after death could truly be, and what happens to an unfortunate few.

Casting Call:

**Director/Camera Operator: **I plan to film this project myself if necessary. Although I lack professional equipment, there will be scenes better handled by someone with more expertise in this area.

**Tex (20-30s Female):** Edgy and sarcastic with a sharp wit, charisma comes naturally to her with a goth/emo aesthetic.

**Scoob (20-30s Male): **A straight-talking rebel to the system, rocker/gothic aesthetic similar to Tex. Heavy smoker on the path to degeneracy.

**Pol (20-30s Female): **Academically astute yet magnetized toward those who follow unconventional paths, supportive and generally well-meaning.

**Rhys (20+ Male): **Through and through an objectivist, studying and research are his bread and butter. The archivist and quiet guide of the group, with an intellectually introverted disposition.

items.summary:
Casting directors don‚Äôt often tell you what actually makes them say yes‚Ä¶
Tomorrow you can ask one directly.
We‚Äôve got the brilliant Nicci Topping joining us LIVE for an online workshop ‚Äî and it‚Äôs a rare chance to hear exactly what she looks for when actors submit, self-tape and walk into the room.
Bring your questions. Bring your curiosity.
These sessions are always honest, practical and usually eye-opening.
üìÖ Tomorrow ‚Äî 18th Feb
üé≠ Live online workshop
üîó Booking link below
If you‚Äôve ever wondered why one tape lands and another doesn‚Äôt‚Ä¶ this is the one to come to.

Im looking for a job as a singer Short-term contract
I am a versatile singer. I sing all types of music( jazz , pop , rock , arabic , french , english a little bit of spanish and italian ) and actress . (I have a strong stage presence and I interact naturally with the audience) . 

Contact me on : +21699903411 or instagram: saharmzidofficial .

items.text:
# **We are searching for people who have ****spectacular stories**** to be told!!!**

Do you have, or know someone, who has an incredible story to be told? Patience Productions is making a 15 minute documentary and are seeking people who want to share their journey! üéûÔ∏è

‚úÖ Have you overcome a major challenge

‚úÖ Have you been in a unique experience?

‚úÖ Do you have an opinion you feel passionate about?

‚úÖ SHARE YOUR JOURNEY. INSPIRE OTHERS.

üé• DETAILS:
* This is a student documentary, and therefore it is non-paid.
* We are based in Portsmouth, but filming locations can be discussed!

**APPLY NOW!** Email **rishchakraborty@gmail.com** with your story, and we will get back to you!

**DEADLINE TO APPLY: MARCH 1ST 2026**

Time to audition for Pivot‚Äôs next show, John Murrell‚Äôs Canadian classic: ‚ÄúWaiting for the Parade‚Äù, directed by Kayt Roth.

On the home front in Calgary during World War II, five women deal with loneliness, infidelity, heartbreak, and friendship as they support the troops, the Red Cross, and each other. This play showcases the women who stayed behind, and focuses on the effect that the war has on them, their relationships, and their families.

Auditions are February 22nd and 23rd at Progress Lab (1422 William Street, Vancouver). Visit https://www.pivottheatre.ca/currentauditions for character breakdowns and all the details!

#PivotTheatre #WaitingForTheParade #YVRTheatre #TheatreBC #AuditionsVancouver

items.title: Background Call

items.text:
CASTING CALL

Project: indie film

Plot:

A woman in her 20s drifts through friendships, impulses, and quiet disappointments, unsure of who she is or how to move forward. As her world begins to fracture, she is forced to confront her own patterns of blame, desire, and avoidance. Through solitude and fleeting human connections, she slowly learns to sit with sadness, not as something to escape, but as a guide toward self-understanding and the courage to begin again.

 

Shooting dates: Mid-End of March 2026 (mostly weekends)

Shooting location: Vancouver and the greater area

 

Please submit your resume, headshot(s), and demo reel or self-tape by email: [theprivilegeofsorrow@gmail.com](mailto:theprivilegeofsorrow@gmail.com)

 

Volunteer Position

 

PARTY FRIEND #1

Male, 20s

Cocky, confrontational party goer. Loves night thrills; beach partying, running, shouting, high energy after a wild house party.

 

PARTY FRIEND #2

Male/female/non-binary, 20s

Easygoing follower, impulsive and playful. Down for anything; night beach run, laughing, hyping the group, physical, carefree energy.

 

PARTY FRIEND #3

Male/female/non-binary, 20s

At a chaotic party, they notice a girl passed out. Later, in a quieter moment, they end up talking while the party continues.

 

GLASSES

Male, 20s
Tall, robust, dominant presence. Confident, physical, impulsive; intense hookup energy in a crowded party setting.

 

GYM EMPLOYEE

Neutral, mildly defensive, trained to de-escalate. Repeats policy language automatically, avoids eye contact, prioritizes rules over empathy.

 

GAS STATION WORKER

Irritable, territorial, quick to escalate. Defensive authority figure; confrontational energy in a late-night, mundane conflict over a vending machine.

 

We are also casting background performers for the party scenes. Please indicate your interest when submitting.

items.text:
CASTING CALL: THE COLLECTOR (Short Film)

Production: Independent Short Film

Genre: Supernatural Horror / Psychological Thriller

Location: York, England

Shoot Dates: April 12th and 13th

Compensation: Unpaid. Catering provided. This project is intended as the beginning of an ongoing creative collaboration.

Synopsis:

The Collector explores the predatory nature of darkness and the dangerous misunderstanding of vulnerability. Innocence is not seen as purity, but as something to be consumed.

Roles Available:

Grace (Female, 40s) Lead

A composed, intelligent professional with a quiet but formidable presence. Calm, controlled, and shaped by survival.

Emma (Female, 14‚Äì15) Lead

Curious and isolated. Emotionally intuitive and observant. Becomes the focus of the Entity‚Äôs attention.

The Entity (Female) Supporting

A physical, unsettling presence of pale flesh and darkness. Strong physical performance required. Heavy makeup FX and sclera lenses involved.

David (Male, late 30s to 40s) Supporting

Emma‚Äôs father. Practical and protective, pushed into a terrifying supernatural confrontation.

Father Benedict (Male, 60s) Supporting

A frail but determined priest attempting an exorcism. Spiritually authoritative despite physical weakness.

Submission Requirements:

Please click on the Google forms link below to submit your answers: https://forms.gle/sbUWJAjRM8iJmJFMA

POSITION: Company Stage Manager

RATE OF PAY: ¬£200 per 2 show day plus accommodation and PD's.

LOCATION: National UK theatre tour

DESCRIPTION: We are looking for a Company Stage Manager for a National children's theatre tour of 'Fireman Sam Live'. Main duties will be Load ins/outs and show cues during the show. They will also share the driving of the touring Luton van with the rest of the crew. As a result the successful candidate will need to be 25 and over for insurance purposes. Please send CV's to marc.featherstone@mt-productions.co.uk

items.text:
Hello Everyone,

My name is Shaun Daly and I currently in early development of producing a brand-new TV show titled ‚ÄòLOCAL TALENT‚Äô. Written and to be directed the talented Bethany McGiveron. The show is set in a town in the North West of England, where in a working-class neighbourhood, a brothel disguised as a ‚Äúsauna‚Äù to the public resides. Within this brothel, we follow the group of women who own, manage and work there. All of whom are an array of characters who get along like a chosen family that will do whatever they can for each other. Helping one another to survive in this modern world that they are all struggling to survive in and catch moments of joy that life is meant to bring to them. 

The show is inspired a little by the Channel 4 documentary A Very British Brothel, along with stories and accounts of people who have worked in the industry. Stories and accounts we are still researching into now. The vibe and tone of the show is a drama/comedy like the likes of the UK Shameless and Brassic to name some examples. It is a show about together, positivity, banter amongst what the characters would consider are their chosen family. However, along with that, each character has their own personal conflicts, struggles, secrets and desperation for survival.

Our plan is to create a pitch package for the series, by producing the pilot episode. Looking to be around 45 to an hour maximum. We are currently in pre-production and are looking to film around the North West, anywhere from Wirral, Liverpool, St Helens and further if necessary.

What we are looking for is talented actors and actresses from around the North West who would be interested in playing the roles below. Warning that the show will explore themes of a sexual nature along with themes of survival and togetherness. Characters will be dressing up in sexy attire for clients and be performing suggestive positions, simulated sexual content and light fetish comedy as well. No intention of nudity to be involved.

If you‚Äôre comfortable with this, then please see the roles below and email shaundaly2510@gmail.com:

**CHELSEA**

Female, 30s,

Curvy, expressive, intimidating and hilarious. A dominatrix with sharp wit and a soft interior she hides well. Natural scouser who has moved away from her past in Liverpool and has found a home working as the Dominatrix of the brothel. Confident, funny, a strong presence within the Brothel.

**LYDIA**

Female, 30s ‚Äì 40s.

Main villain of Series 1. Sharp, polished, cold underneath. Controlling, emotionally volatile. Very manipulative. Knows her beauty can seduce and make slaves of those who fall under her spell. Character will be exploring themes of domestic violence.

**SHIRLEY**

Female, late 30s ‚Äì early 40s.

Body Positive, full figured, curvy, tom boyish character. Short practical hair. Dry humour and fiercely loyal. Childhood best friend of Tammy.

**TAMMY**

Female, late 30s ‚Äì early 40s.

Body Positive, full figured, voluptuous, bubbly, girly, cheerful. Loyal, excitable, forms a comedic duo with Shirley. Warm and expressive. Can be nervous and frantic.

**BIG LIZ**

Trans masculine or non-binary performer, 40s ‚Äì 50s.

Large frame, camp, emotional, theatrical. Switching between dramatic monologues and silly vulnerability. Use of masculine & feminine voice. Strong, comedic, like the mother hen of the group. With only the Manger Julie above them. Seen as second in command and protector of everyone who works for the Brothel.

**MARY** (Receptionist)

Female, 20s - 30s.

Receptionist of the Brothel. Organises all the clients, answers phones, sorts the lunches and evening meals, arranges the rotas for everyone working at the Brothel. She is small, gentle-looking, quietly stressed. The admin backbone of the brothel in the neat office that is seen when you walk in.

**ROSALINE**

Female, 30s.

Slim or average build, messy glamour, clearly exhausted. A touring girl whose unravelling emotional state becomes part of the plot. Mainly featured in the Pilot, may be planned to return for later episodes.

**BLOSSOM**

Female, Dark Skin Toned, late 30s‚Äì40s.

A Nigerian woman who works for the Brothel. She is elegant, expressive, deeply emotional. Balances trauma, fear, and warmth. She has come from a tough background and has come to the UK for a better life. For her, working at the Brothel is that better life, compared to the life she had back in Nigeria. She is kind and considerate, but still afraid to stand up for herself. Especially when it comes to her stalker Ade.

**ADE**

Male, dark skin tone, 40s - 50s.

Tall, intimidating, deeply unsettling. Stalker presence, threatening. Strong physical presence. Very smug and cocky. To the point of unbearable. 

**DARREN** (Blossom love interest)

Male, 30s‚Äì40s.

Short man, sweet, warm, confident but sensitive. Blossoms love interest and the opposite of Ade. Darren is in love with Blossom and is happy just to spend time with her and even wants to embrace her culture and be a part of her life. He is looked down upon and seen as too soft, especially from Ade. But there is more to Darren than meets the eye.

**NIGEL**

Male, late 30s‚Äì50s.

Soft, friendly, policeman. Awkward. Very innocent and na√Øve. Stuff that goes on in the brothel could be seen to make him feel uncomfortable. Good hearted individual.

**STEVE (Office Pennington, Policeman)**

Male, late 20s‚Äì30s.

Stiff, easily flustered police officer. Easily manipulated. Tries to act all hard and tough when he is just a pawn for a bigger scheme to be revealed later in the series. Entangled with Lydia.

üî• TWO POWERFUL DANCE SOLOS AT KNAP! üî•
üìÖ December 10, 2025 at 7 PM
üìç KNAP ‚Äì Concert Hall, Ivaniƒágradska 41a, Zagreb
‚ú® FREE ENTRY!

Join us for a captivating evening within KNAP‚Äôs Offbeat program, featuring two striking solo performances that delve deep into the questions of identity, transformation, and the inevitability of change.

In I SAMO, choreographer and performer Bruno Isakoviƒá confronts the modern obsession with constant self-improvement. Through an intimate, physical dialogue, the piece dismantles the myth of the ‚Äúbetter version of oneself‚Äù and opens a space for sincerity, vulnerability, and authentic presence.

In KRAJ KRAJEVA, performed by Mia Zalukar, the focus shifts toward the countless endings‚Äîsubtle, unexpected, or monumental‚Äîthat punctuate our daily lives. The work invites us to reflect on how we face closure, what we resist or accept, and how endings might quietly reframe our beginnings.

Together, these two solos offer a powerful meditation on who we are while striving, changing, finishing, and beginning again. Expect an evening of deeply felt movement, thought-provoking concepts, and artists who approach the stage with uncompromising honesty.

üéüÔ∏è Free tickets available at the link in the first comment.
Don‚Äôt miss this unique double bill!

U svijetu u kojem se od nas tra≈æi da budemo ‚Äûbolje verzije sebe‚Äú, Bruno Isakoviƒá u svom solo komadu razotkriva paradoks osobnog rasta: ≈°to ako je ≈æelja za neprekidnim usavr≈°avanjem samo zamka ‚Äî i ako zapravo najvi≈°e rastemo kad dopustimo sebi da ne budemo savr≈°eni?
‚ÄûI samo‚Äú je koreografski poziv na iskrenost, ranjivost i autentiƒçnost, na tijelo koje ne glumi hologram nego govori istinu.

‚∏ª

KRAJ KRAJEVA

üë§ Koreografija i izvedba: Mia Zalukar
üéº Glazba: Hrvoje Nik≈°iƒá
üìù Dramaturgija: Margareta Sinkoviƒá
üé® Umjetniƒçka suradnica: Lucija Bari≈°iƒá
üé¨ Produkcija: UO Malo sutra
üé≠ Koprodukcija: Domino

Koliko ‚Äûkrajeva‚Äú mo≈æemo do≈æivjeti u jednom jedinom danu? I mo≈æemo li ih prepoznati, oznaƒçiti, ispratiti?
U solo izvedbi ‚ÄûKraj krajeva‚Äú, Mia Zalukar otvara prostor za razgovor s neizbje≈ænim zavr≈°ecima ‚Äî onim krupnim i onim sitnim, svakodnevnim. Kroz cikliƒçnu izvedbu, pokret i promi≈°ljanje, ona stvara intiman dijalog s prolazno≈°ƒáu i propituje kako se pripremamo za kraj‚Ä¶ i ≈°to se dogodi kad ga napokon prihvatimo.

‚∏ª

üéüÔ∏è Ulaz slobodan ‚Äî pridru≈æite nam se na veƒçeri koja otvara prostor za promjenu, prihvaƒáanje i novo gledanje na sebe i svijet.

Tall and skinny, wired with perpetually self-conscious energy; he carries himself like

someone rejected while auditioning for manhood. He wants

‚Äúbig dick energy‚Äù the way other people want for oxygen‚Äîstatus, respect, the ability to walk into a room and feel untouchable‚Äîbut a humiliating one-night stand forces him into a same-day escalating series of ‚Äúprotocols‚Äù to attain for himself what God did not give. This actor has to sell physical comedy with finesse: micro-expressions, posture, breath control, the slow collapse when his body just can‚Äôt go that last... inch. A dead-seriously-overinflated ‚ÄúWick‚Äù fa√ßade at the end, once he himself begins to believe.

THE HOOKUP (22‚Äì30 years old) - Female, any ethnicity

A dating-app one-night stand with sharp instincts and a mouth that

moves faster than anyone‚Äôs sense of empathy. She wants a simple quid-

pro-quo, but when Dick‚Äôs situation is revealed, she treats this revelation

like an inconvenience, but not before tagging him with one cutting line

that becomes his inescapable inciting wound. The role is short and

high-impact; it needs an actor who can land brutal lines so starkly they

are humorous, then watch him scramble through eyes that say: ‚ÄúAnd

this is your problem.‚Äù

THE REVEAL (20‚Äì30 years old) - Female, any ethnicity (petite strongly preferred; 4‚Äô10‚Äù ideal)

The final door-open reveal: petite, and grounded enough to make the

absurd visual comparison hit harder. She wants an ordinary date; instead, she

meets a guy who shows up dressed like a hitman, walking like he lost a

bet with his own anatomy, both arms needed to carry the Wal-Mart bag‚Äôs

worth of ‚Äòresults‚Äô. This actor anchors the film‚Äôs ending with restraint and

presence‚Äîreal reactions, steady eye contact, and a line delivery that

punctures Dick‚Äôs hero-fantasy-balloon down to reality in one beat.

THE VOICE (30‚Äì60 years old) - Male, any ethnicity (voiceover role)

A Danny Trejo-style presence in audio form: gravelly, streetwise, yet weirdly sincere

and encouraging. The ‚ÄúI‚Äôve seen it all‚Äù authority of a guy who can talk you into trouble while making it sound like your personal salvation is key. He sells the protocol as if it‚Äôs hard-earned knowledge, and that means equal parts tough-love coach, back-alley mentor, late-night infomercial pitchman, and a pinch of Roganesque ‚Äòmanosphere‚Äô vibe. Always steering Dick toward the ‚Äònext step‚Äô with confident certainty, yet crooked sense of humor. The performance needs conviction and range: persuasive warmth, a threatening edge when his ‚Äòdisciples‚Äô hesitate, and the steady escalation of ritualistic, almost spell-like instructions that make the ridiculous feel like an inevitable success.

items.text:
Casting call!!!!
Hey everyone, I'm just about halfway done casting for my upcoming romance film "A Handful of Love and Demons to Hate" based on a novel just published! The roles listed below are what I'm still in need of, so a character you can portray just send it to the email provided and follow the instructions on the flyer. I can't wait to get started soon and I look forward to everyone's submission. This does take place in GA and filming will start sometime in April. I plan to be finished by mid July. This is non paid however you will receive credit so just letting everyone know. To offset not being able to pay those brining my production together, I will be hosting a wrap up event/party for the last day of filming, offering low price novel copies to the cast instead of regular price, and sending you early access of the finished movie product that way you can see it before it comes out. Also you might have to click on the pictures of the roles because they can look blurry/pixelated at first then they clear up

üåü Reserving Royalty Casting Call Seeking New Performer üåü
Reserving Royalty is currently seeking to add an additional performer to our professional character cast with a specific need for a performer wishing to play the coveted roles of Elphaba and Tiana (along with other opportunities in our roster). We are looking for a candidate who wants consistent weekend work and who enjoys working with children and is ready to embody these beloved characters and bring them to life for triad families! 

üëë Email your submission to: Hello@reservingroyalty.com
üì© Subject line: CASTING
Please include:
‚ú® Full Name
‚ú® Phone Number
‚ú® Available Start Date
‚ú® Typical Weekend Availability Schedule
‚ú® Two current headshots (one full smile showing teeth & one without a smile)
‚ú® One current waist-up photo
‚ú® One current full-body photo
(Photos do not need to be professional, just clear and current! We wig every character)
üé§ Video Audition:
Please also consider submitting a video of you singing a princess  / Disney song of your choice that best showcases your vocal range. Sing-along style is totally fine, as long as we can hear that you can carry a tune! We sing Happy birthday alot around here!
Performers selected to move forward will be contacted by RR Casting for the next round, which will be an in-person interview at our location.

CASTING CALL 

Open Door Collective is seeking an actor with Down syndrome for a lead role in Are We Friends?, a new two-hander play premiering at Camden Fringe Festival 2026.

Note that this is a Camden Fringe production with a limited budget. What we‚Äôre able to offer is:

‚Ä¢ A 50/50 split of ticket sales between the two actors (after the festival cut)

‚Ä¢ Travel expenses covered

No prior acting experience is required ‚Äî just curiosity, openness, and a love of storytelling. Rehearsals will take place in London, in a supportive, accessible environment.

To apply, please send:

‚Ä¢ A headshot (or clear photo)

 ‚Ä¢ A short, informal introduction video

Apply here: [https://forms.gle/gL5zgNWfAQDfE1Xv5](https://forms.gle/gL5zgNWfAQDfE1Xv5?fbclid=IwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTAAYnJpZBExdGZ0MGo5ZGlXaXp1OEtKZ3NydGMGYXBwX2lkEDIyMjAzOTE3ODgyMDA4OTIAAR75cMcxzNDbhsItHH_YdjJ6rWnphpz6CxPeOQx4rinczBkP8I3rW5aqPejwnA_aem_6R0DHJ4OAt2hDXIKZMjNSw)

Rose Waite Studio is looking for individuals, friends, colleagues and families (18+) with varying attitudes towards football ‚Äî from die-hard to indifferent ‚Äî for a World Cup promotional campaign.

Whether you‚Äôre already planning your sweepstakes or you might tolerate the odd match, we‚Äôd love to hear from you. We want to capture the general public from all walks of life and approaches to football.

Talent must be comfortable on set as well as self-shooting.

Filming / Self Shooting Period: 16 March - 10 April

UK-based talent. Paid opportunity. No previous experience needed to apply.

To apply, please email stories@rosewaite.com with the subject ‚ÄòWorld Cup Campaign‚Äô.

Please include:
Name / Age / Profession / Location / Selfie
Your Attitude Towards Football
The team(s) you support (if any)

items.text:
CASTING CALL - ‚ÄúThe Sins of Our Father‚Äù
Hi everyone! My name is Emma and I‚Äôm the associate producer for the upcoming feature film The Sins of Our Father. We are excited to be starting our casting process! 

Filming will be taking place mid May to early August, every second weekend approximately (tentatively), in the greater Vancouver area. It is a volunteer project (with IMDb credit, copy, and great company). This will be a UBCP ultra low budget feature film. 

If you are interested in being apart of this amazing project please email your demo reel, resume, and the name of the character you‚Äôre auditioning for to thesinsofourfatherfilm@gmail.com by March 8th.

Synopsis:

The Sins of Our Father dissects the crumbling legacy of the Montgomery family in a narrative that blends gritty family drama with surreal, lo-fi sci-fi.

The story begins with Clive, a dying pawnshop owner and lifelong hustler who attempts one final con: using a mysterious, memory-altering projector to force a reconciliation with his estranged children. With his twisted understanding of fatherhood, he plans to "overwrite" their trauma to stage one final, perfect memory.

The film unfolds in an exploration of the fallouts with his three children: Maddie, the eldest, paralyzed by the fear of inheriting her father‚Äôs toxicity; Leland, a debt-ridden filmmaker shooting adult content to survive; and Julian, a recluse who has signed a "deal with the devil" by accepting tuition sponsorship from Clive‚Äôs ruthless rival, Vance.

The plan shatters when Clive misuses the device. As the siblings uncover the truth, their own demons collide with external threats‚Äîincluding Vance and a gang of "trustafarian" loan sharks‚Äîwho descend on the family home to seize the mysterious projector.

In a chaotic climax that blurs the line between memory and reality, the siblings must weaponize the device to escape. Ultimately, Clive makes the only selfless choice of his life, resulting in his children finally being free.

attachments.ocrText: May be an image of text that says 'Casting Call THE SINS OF OUR FATHER Are you more than the sum of your father's S mistakes?'

May be an image of text that says 'Main MainCast Cast CLIVE 60s, MALE, WHITE Stubborn. Proud. Assertive. A lifelong grifter and owner of Vancouver's S last independent pawnshop. Clive treated fatherhood like a transaction he could negotiate Too proud to apologize for the trauma he inflicted, he views the memory- altering projector not as a sci-fi miracle, but as the ultimate "fix" to reunite his dysfunctional family.'

May be an image of text that says 'Main Cast MADDIE 35, FEMALE, WHITE/BIRACIAL BIRACIAL Analytical. Caring. Avoidant. Clive's eldest daughter whose fear of becoming her father has paralyzed her ability to move forward. Terrified that her "fucked up" lineage makes her unfit for motherhood, she over-analyzes every aspect of her life and avoids her emotions to avoid making irrational mistakes.'

May be a graphic of one or more people and text that says 'Main MainCas Cast Phon LELAND 30, MALE, WHITE WHITE/BIRACIAL BIRACIAL Free-spirited. Lax. Unbothered. Deep in debt to dangerous "trustafarians" Leland, who is director of adult content, is the result of Clive pushing him too hard to succeed in field he wasn't interested in; now, having taken huge risk by pursuing filmmaking he is paralyzed, afraid that his unsuccessful filmmaking career will prove Clive right.'

May be an image of text that says 'Main MainCast Cast JULIAN 24, MALE, WHITE/BIRACIAL Geeky. Sentimental. Quick-witted. The youngest and damaged by the need for Œ± father figure A university student with commitment issues and knack for repairing broken electronics. Alienated by Clive, Julian has signed 'deal with the devil," accepting tuition sponsorship from Clive' arch-rival, Vance -a decision that legally binds him to the villain.'

items.text: I need advice on how much I should realistically expect to spend for a short 5 minute film. Assuming i want the video and audio quality of a legitimate production. I have the script ready to go, however I need a crew. I am serving as writer, director, and actor so i need a director of photography, sound recordist, Costume/makeup person, editor, plus 1 more actor and 1 more actress.  I LIVE IN HOUSTON TEXAS.

Casting : "Maybe its love, maybe not"

I am Thomas Goersch from Stuttgart Germany. 
Actor and Filmdirector. 
I am making Independent Movies.
I present my movies on International Film festivals and was lucky to receive some awards. 
But the work is not about awards and money, its about making movies for the people to think about.
My next movie is a modern love story:
An elderly man is meeting another younger, very attractive man in the Internet.  But they are from different Continents. They start a long distance relastionship ship. which is full of passion and desire. 
One day the younger man starts to ask for money, cause he is a Student and no more able to pay his bills. 
The older man is full of distrust.
Is he only there  to pay his lovers bills or is there love between them ?
A story with two endings.
One with true love and one with only cheating. Based on a real story.
I am looking for the young attraktive Lover.
Men  25 to 42 years old,  good looking  who is able to film his parts on his own by smartshone
I am always open and honest. You can earn no money on this. but maybe there is a good film in the end promoting for you.
I guess its not necessary that an educated actor is playing this part. so feel free to get in touch
Thats me 
www.imdb.com/name/nm1591928
Get in touch under Thomas.Goersch@vodafonemail.de 
please ask for details.

‚ö°Ô∏èNeed to create your first showreel / freshen up your old one?‚ö°Ô∏è
Happy Sunday all!

I provide a very affordable showreel service for new or established actors/directors/cinematographers/comedians/hobbyists etc.

Basically, send me your footage (or I can try and source it for you online if it's commercially aired) and I shall edit it together into a lovely reel.

Please see samples of recent clients in the link below üòé

I'm an actor myself so I know how frustrating it can be, especially when you're starting out, to collate your footage together to get more work, without wanting to spend a fortune.

My rates are ¬£20/hour, with duration of work depending on how much footage you have. The average reels have been around ¬£80-¬£100 for my clients. Much more affordable than the companies that charge ¬£250+ !!

For any further info / enquiries / to book my services, drop me an email and I'll respond as quickly as I can:

reelsforanyone@gmail.com

I'll look forward to hearing from you.

Thanks!

üòé

www.youtube.com/@Reels.For.Anyone

items.text:
**Casting Call - Musical Puppet Short Film in Bristol!**

We are looking for anyone interested in musical theatre or actors to perform our puppets in our graduate student short film 'The Grand Puppet Heist'. No prior puppeteering experience necessary just lots of enthusiasm to bring these characters to life and perfect for anyone interested in musical theatre or comedy! Our lead 'Barry the Baker' is a strong musical theatre role and would be great opportunity for a performer - still looking for interest for all roles still at this stage. See the casting poster for more info and see the characters! 

We are also casting three human supporting roles which would be very fun roles to fill - for our talk show host, director and Bartender 'Cam'. See the casting poster for more info.

All roles will include all expenses of food and travel covered but due to the low budget nature are unpaid - all support of this project will be greatly appreciated and its assured to be fun collaborative one. Rehearsals at the start of March with filming dates between the 16th and 25th March in Bristol.

Please email **Tyler.beck@boomsatsuma.education** if interested. Thanks so much!
